Once upon a time, in a small village nestled in the hills of a lush green valley, lived two young lovers, Arar and Btr. Arar was a skilled carpenter, known for his craftsmanship and attention to detail, while Btr was a beautiful and talented weaver, admired for her intricate designs and vibrant colors. The two had known each other since childhood and had always been inseparable. As they grew older, their bond deepened, and they soon realized that they were in love. They spent many long afternoons by the riverbank, talking and dreaming about their future together. Despite their deep love for each other, Arar and Btr came from different worlds. Arar's family were carpenters, while Btr's family were weavers, and the two trades did not often mix. However, their love was stronger than any societal or familial barriers, and they vowed to be together no matter what. One day, Arar decided to build a special gift for Btr, a beautiful wooden loom with intricate carvings and smooth edges. Btr was overjoyed with the gift and immediately began to weave a beautiful tapestry on it. As the weeks went by, the two worked side by side, with Arar building beautiful furniture for the village, and Btr weaving exquisite tapestries and blankets. Despite the long hours and hard work, they never lost sight of their love for each other. One evening, as the sun was setting, Arar and Btr sat by the riverbank, holding hands and watching the stars. Arar turned to Btr and said, "My love, I cannot imagine a life without you. Will you marry me and be my partner in life and work?" Btr's eyes filled with tears of joy, and he threw his arms around Arar, saying, "Yes, my love, I will marry you and be with you always." And so, Arar and Btr were married in a beautiful ceremony, with the entire village in attendance. They continued to work side by side, with Arar building the most beautiful furniture for their home, while Btr wove intricate tapestries that adorned their walls. Their love story became the talk of the village, inspiring other couples to follow their hearts and break down barriers to be together. And Arar and Btr lived happily ever after, their love and commitment to each other stronger than ever before.
